_________________________________________<br>
<br>
I said goodbye to you, little cat.<br>
fingers caught on bones when I stroked your fur.<br>
You could scarcely raise your head to drink,<br>
Yet still you calmed me with your purr.<br>
<br>
Were you comfortable curled on the rug?<br>
And did you know your time drew near?<br>
Your wide blue eyes held gentle love,<br>
And quiet pain, but showed no fear.<br>
<br>
You slipped away so quietly<br>
that we weren't sure you were gone.<br>
Our bouncy little cat is stilled,<br>
But your spirit lingers on.<br>
<br>
Little ghost cat, where are you?<br>
Are you happy, are you strong?<br>
I feel your warmth, your life, your love<br>
And can still hear your purring song.<br>
